<p>
	It belongs to the Corund group and is, after the diamond, the second hardest mineral in all of nature. Its colour is given by chromium and the presence of brownish tones is due to the existence of iron in its chemical composition. Burma, Thailand, Ceylon and Tanzania are the most important mining areas. During certain periods of the year, the largest marketplace of precious stone-gems in the world takes place in Chanthaburi (Thailand): to buy there is a challenge to specialists.
